        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 4:35PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong winds ahead of a
line from near Westwood Colony to near Verdon to 7 miles west of
Spottswood. Movement was south at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Redfield, Webster, Groton, Britton, Veblen, Bristol, Langford,
Tulare, Roslyn, Doland, Glendale Colony, Frankfort, Sunset Colony,
Conde, Pierpont, Spink Colony, Hillside Colony, Ashton, Newport
Colony, and Hutterville Colony.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
northeastern South Dakota.</instruction>
